otonic. Cross-process replay with fan-in   writers is explicitly deferred — see <code>docs/dev-log.md</code> Phase 5 notes."}}],["$","ul","14",{"children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong>Encryption-agnostic.</strong> The bus stores raw bytes; wrap the provider"}}]]}],["$","p","15",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"  with <code>encrypted(...)</code> and the whole log is AES-GCM-sealed to a KEK   derived from an EOA signer."}}],["$","ul","16",{"children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<strong>Deterministic replay.</strong> <code>replay()</code> returns events in seq order with"}}]]}],["$","p","17",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"  stable keys so tests and audits can diff the log across runs."}}],["$","h2","18",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Patterns"}}],["$","p","19",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<code>planExecuteCritique</code> is the one shipped v0 pattern. Debate and hierarchical patterns are deferred to a future phase — see <code>docs/dev-log.md</code>. You can build your own pattern by composing <code>mesh.bus.append(...)</code> and <code>agent.run(...)</code> directly; there is nothing privileged about <code>planExecuteCritique</code>."}}],["$","h2","20",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Further reading"}}],["$","ul","21",{"children":[["$","li","0",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<a href=\"../../examples/research-mesh\"><code>examples/research-mesh</code></a> — 3-agent DoD demo with an encrypted 0G Log bus."}}],["$","li","1",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<a href=\"../../docs/benchmarks.md\"><code>docs/benchmarks.md</code></a> — tasks/second on Galileo + free router."}}],["$","li","2",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"<a href=\"../../docs/architecture.md\"><code>docs/architecture.md</code></a> — how Bus, Mesh and agents fit in the layered stack."}}]]}],["$","h2","22",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"License"}}],["$","p","23",{"dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":